<Link id="l00281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="281"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Tracks whether the accesses may be on different cycle iterations.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00283" /><CodeLine lineNumber="283"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// When interpret &quot;Value&quot; pointer equality as value equality we need to make</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00284" /><CodeLine lineNumber="284"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// sure that the &quot;Value&quot; is not part of a cycle. Otherwise, two uses could</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00285" /><CodeLine lineNumber="285"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// come from different &quot;iterations&quot; of a cycle and see different values for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the same &quot;Value&quot; pointer.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="287"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The following example shows the problem:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   %p = phi(%alloca1, %addr2)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   %l = load %ptr</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   %addr1 = gep, %alloca2, 0, %l</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   %addr2 = gep  %alloca2, 0, (%l + 1)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///      alias(%p, %addr1) -&gt; MayAlias !</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   store %l, ...</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/aaqueryinfo/#ad146481f5f2cf1cad3e6174f4398ecbe"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/aaqueryinfo/#ad146481f5f2cf1cad3e6174f4398ecbe">MayBeCrossIteration</a> = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Whether alias analysis is allowed to use the dominator tree, for use by</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This class is a wrapper over an AAResults, and it is intended to be used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><Highlight kind="comment">/// only when there are no IR changes inbetween queries. BatchAAResults is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><Highlight kind="comment">/// reusing the same &#96;AAQueryInfo&#96; to preserve the state across queries,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"><Highlight kind="comment">/// esentially making AA work in &quot;batch mode&quot;. The internal state cannot be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><Highlight kind="comment">/// cleared, so to go &quot;out-of-batch-mode&quot;, the user must either use AAResults,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><Highlight kind="comment">/// or create a new BatchAAResults.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/batchaaresults"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/batchaaresults/#a3d71ed97284d930cf65f86bdc35c1dce">BatchAAResults</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/aaresults">AAResults</a> &amp;AA;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/aaqueryinfo">AAQueryInfo</a> AAQI;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="811"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A base class to help implement the function alias analysis results concept.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00812" /><CodeLine lineNumber="812"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00813" /><CodeLine lineNumber="813"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Because of the nature of many alias analysis implementations, they often</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00814" /><CodeLine lineNumber="814"><Highlight kind="comment">/// only implement a subset of the interface. This base class will attempt to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00815" /><CodeLine lineNumber="815"><Highlight kind="comment">/// implement the remaining portions of the interface in terms of simpler forms</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="816"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of the interface where possible, and otherwise provide conservatively</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="817"><Highlight kind="comment">/// correct fallback implementations.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="818"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00819" /><CodeLine lineNumber="819"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Implementors of an alias analysis should derive from this class, and then</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="820"><Highlight kind="comment">/// override specific methods that they wish to customize. There is no need to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00821" /><CodeLine lineNumber="821"><Highlight kind="comment">/// use virtual anywhere.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00822" /><CodeLine lineNumber="822" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/aaresultbase"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/aaresultbase/#adda3309ea19cc0a7a0bcb090630bbfc4">AAResultBase</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
